  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-01 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; six achieve their required level and seven carry documented justifications for partial achievement. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is applied across the majority of validation results. Decision: Accepted on the basis of compensating controls and documented residual gaps. This package is a synthetic adversarial sample designed to trigger COMPOUND-01: the bound Claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance link (W-EP-01, Critical) and one ValidationResult omits hasUncertaintyQuantification (W-AL-01, High).",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v3",
