      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index prediction — bench comparison",
      "description": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) predicted by the power-law hemolysis model is compared against in-vitro bovine blood measurements at three operating points. Predicted NIH falls within the inter-laboratory variability band reported in the FDA benchmark dataset. This result constitutes the primary credibility evidence for the hemolysis claim. Note: uncertainty quantification for this result was deferred pending completion of the sensitivity study on hemolysis model exponent uncertainty; no hasUncertaintyQuantification node is attached to this ValidationResult."
